This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it introduces a new framework for learning filters that can be applied to tasks such as video and stereo prediction. It is also likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories as it proposes a new architecture for neural networks. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of recurrent architectures, which could place it in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed framework on the moving MNIST dataset, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
